author: jkuhnert
msg: Fixed made for for TAPESTRY-1066. The overall solution ended being using a combination of object.hashCode()
functions on the server end as well as attaching these unique function names to the global client side
tapestry object. Doing this allows a consistent unique name to be generated for functions, which also allows us to
call dojo.event.disconnect to ensure multiple listeners aren't added accidently.

author: jacopoc
msg: First pass in the implementation of the user interface to create, in the order entry checkout process, more than one ship group.
It is now possible to create ship groups and set different addresses and options for them but it is still not possible to assign the products in the cart to them.
I'm going to start the implementation of a new checkout screen that will allow this.
